-- Philippine bourse says trading halted on technical issues 
-- 
-- Mon May 05, 2014 01:24AM EDT
-- None



MANILA, May 5 (Reuters) - The Philippine Stock Exchange <PSE.PS> said trading on the local bourse was halted from 11:02 a.m. (0302 GMT) on Monday, citing "technical issues", and did not indicate when trading will resume.

Trading in the local bourse normally resumes at 1:30 p.m. after a mid-day break from 12 noon. The main index <.PSI> was flat before the trading halt.